'''''Mar<U+00ED>a del Mar''''' is a Venezuelan [[telenovela]] produced by [[Venevisi<U+00F3>n]] in 1978. An original story by veteran telenovela writer Delia Fiallo, it starred [[Chelo Rodr<U+00ED>guez]] and [[Arnaldo Andr<U+00E9>]] as the main protagonists with [[Hilda Carrero]] and [[Mart<U+00ED>n Lantigua]] as the antagonists.<ref>[http://www.vencor.narod.ru/films/mariamar.htm VENEVISION (1978) Maria del Mar]</ref>

==Plot==
In a village along the coast of Venezuela lives  Maria Celeste, a girl with big dreams who is very cheerful and rebellious. She has been raised up by a kind family of fishermen, since she is the product of a rape, and her mother went mad after her delivery. during one summer, the mighty Leonidas Parras Montiel returns to town with his daughters, the selfish engineer Walkiria and the shy Zulay. Also, another person returns to the village: engineer Victor Manuel Galindez, a handsome man who hides a tortuous past. After spending time with each other, Maria Celeste falls in love with Victor Manuel.

Leonidas wants to build a hotel and entrusts the project to Walkiria and Victor Manuel. Immediately they fall in love, but he is fascinated with Maria Celeste. Leonidas also falls in love with the humble girl and wants to make her his wife.
But everything will change when Victor Manuel rescues a beautiful and strange woman from the sea, a woman that the villagers  believe is a mermaid. In reality, she is Miriam, a woman who went insane after Leonidas and his family financially destroyed and burned her property, causing the death of her parents and her husband. Victor Manuel dedicates his time in helping this woman, and this causes Mary Celeste to become jealous. Again, a prestigious publisher named Daniel comes into town, and is marvelled at the exotic beauty of Maria Celeste. He offers to take her to the city to make her a model. She agrees and goes with him, adopting the stage name of Maria del Mar. In the city, Maria will fall in love and triumph in the capital, until she becomes paralyzed through an unfortunate accident.<ref>[http://novelasyseries.univision.com/maria-del-mar Mar<U+00ED>a del Mar Univision novelasyseries]</ref><ref>[http://www.network54.com/Forum/223031/message/1181179189/%2A%26quot%3BMar%EDa+del+Mar%26quot%3B%2A%28Venezuela%2C+1978%29%2A Archivo de telenovelas y biografias "Mar<U+00ED>a del Mar"*(Venezuela, 1978)]</ref>

